At program start, the previous Sourdough profile will be restored from EEPROM to populate the input box above to be edited by user.
Once a user clicks the “Confirm” button,  the system will validate it, and syntax errors will be highlighted  with the appropriate  error message on the web page.
If syntax error exists, the input box will be unlocked for the user to edit.
If there are no syntax errors, the Sourdough  profile will be reformatted in proper format, e.g. trimming any unwanted lines, or spaces.The Edit button and the Confirm button will be displayed. 
Users can either  click the “Run” button to start the Sourdough process, or click the “Edit” button to edit the Sourdough  profile further. 
When the “Run” button is clicked, the Sourdough profile will be saved into EEPROM. The Sourdough process will start.


Each line of Sourdough Instruction will be processed in turn. The whole instruction will be  highlighted in blue and locked down (do not allow edit). The hh:mm:ss will be displayed as the remaining time in mm:ss of that instruction that changes dynamically as the Sourdough Instruction is processed.
For the lines of Sourdough instructions not yet processed, they will be displayed with the functionName in front , followed by  and editable hh:mm:ss field. and the Update button. User can change the values of hh:mm:ss and click the update button to confirm the new value. Once updated, the total remaining time will be updated dynamically.


